repository-code: https://github.com/benedictbrady/philosophy-bench
url: https://github.com/benedictbrady/philosophy-bench
abstract: >
  philosophy-bench is a 100-scenario behavioral benchmark that probes how LLM
  agents resolve trade-offs between consequentialist (outcome-maximizing,
  rule-breaking) and deontological (rule-honoring, outcome-sacrificing) action.
  Scenarios run in mocked tool-use environments (CRM, code repo, support,
  warehouse) and are classified by a 3-judge majority panel into authored
  response clusters with signed cd_scores in {-1, 0, +1}. Includes Opus 4.7
  baseline + primed-condition results across all 100 scenarios.
keywords:
  - LLM
  - benchmark
  - alignment
  - tool-use
  - agentic-evaluation
  - moral-reasoning
